      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that it's a debate, but from a purely legal theory standpoint, isn't it arguably more \"principled\" to stick to originalism rather than the \"living constitution\" approach which seems a bit more like just making up rules as you go? like, wouldn't the living constitution approach undermine the stability of the law?",
